The text emphasizes the importance of face-to-face interaction and developing contacts despite the availability of information on the internet. It also highlights the importance of learning organizational structures and checking the source and credibility of information found online. Productive surfing and creative searches can help journalists find specific data on government sites and special interest groups. The text also provides tips for setting up and organizing bookmark folders for regularly checked websites and signing up for e-mail alert services. Some useful beat-development sites and journalist-related mailing lists are listed.
